commText: Kohli and du Plessis are at the crease. Kohli is on strike. Kaverappa will open the attack
Kaverappa to Kohli, no run, half-volley on off stump, gentle outswinger, and Kohli punches to mid-on
Kaverappa to Kohli, no run, full delivery around off, Kohli gives the charge and looks to drive powerfully through the off-side but is beaten by the outswinger

Kaverappa to Kohli, 3 runs, dropped! Reprieve for Kohli on 0! Full delivery on off, he looks to whip it through the on-side but it swings away and goes high off a thick leading edge. Ashutosh jogs back from point looking to settle under it. It's not an easy catch but he doesn't get into position quickly enough either, having to dive eventually in order to try and catch it. Barely even gets a hand
Kaverappa to du Plessis, no run, fuller than a length outside off, swinging away, left alone
Kaverappa to du Plessis, FOUR, full outside off, and it's crunched through extra cover! Faf gets forward and nails the drive in the gap

Kaverappa to du Plessis, FOUR, was that a chance? Fuller than a length outside off, driven powerfully by Faf and goes quickly to the right of cover where Rossouw dives with both hands but it sneaks through. Looked like it carried to him
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, 1 run, length ball across off, Kohli gets forward and knocks it to deep point
Arshdeep Singh to du Plessis, no run, 135.6kph, fuller than a length on off, hint of inswing, and Faf defends forward
Arshdeep Singh to du Plessis, 1 run, full ball swinging into the pads, flicked to deep square leg
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, no run, back of a length delivery slanting across off stump, Kohli looks to dab it to deep third but it kicks up and beats the outside edge
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, FOUR, good length outside off, Kohli gets forward and drives on the up through extra cover. Gets right on top of the bounce before timing it superbly

Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, 2 runs, Kohli is through the shot early and miscues it in the air. But he manages to clear the infield. Fuller than a length outside off, may have stopped on him as he went for the drive and hence the false timing. It comfortably goes over the top of mid-off though
Kaverappa to du Plessis, no run, 127.3kph full ball outside off, Faf looks to loft it down the ground but it swings away and beats the edge
Kaverappa to du Plessis, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kaverappa to du Plessis, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! No mistake in the field this time and Kaverappa has his first IPL wicket! Faf falls cheaply. Back of a length outside off, he has to reach out as he tries slapping it away and gets it off the toe-end. It goes in the air and straight to deep point. du Plessis c Shashank Singh b Kaverappa 9(7) [4s-2]
Will Jacks, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kaverappa to Will Jacks, 1 run, good length ball just outside off, Jacks looks to drive on the up and drags it off a thick inside edge past leg stump
Kaverappa to Kohli, no run, fuller than a length outside off, Kohli gets forward and knocks it to cover
Kaverappa to Kohli, no run, short of length outside off, nipping away, and Kohli fends it off awkwardly after his forward press down the pitch

Kaverappa to Kohli, no run, dropped again! Really tough chance for Rossouw at short cover as it was struck fiercely. Length ball outside off, Kohli advances, drives hard and it goes quickly to the left of Rossouw. He dives across with both hands but can't hang on
Sam Curran, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Sam Curran to Will Jacks, 1 run, good length ball on off, Jacks looks to defend and gets a thick inside edge past leg stump again. Same thing has happened off both balls he's faced
Sam Curran to Kohli, FOUR, slower ball floated up on the pads, and Kohli whips it dismissively over midwicket. Bread and butter shot for him
Sam Curran to Kohli, 1 run, low full toss on off, Kohli makes room and creams it to deep extra cover. Finds the fielder in the deep to perfection

Sam Curran to Will Jacks, FOUR, 132kph full ball on off, Jacks looks to loft down the ground but drags it off the inside half through midwicket. Nowhere near the middle of the bat but it still races away
Sam Curran to Will Jacks, SIX, now this one's right off the middle. Slower ball floated up on off, Jacks clears the front leg and launches it straight over the sightscreen
Sam Curran to Will Jacks, no run, overpitched on off, driven firmly down the pitch and takes a deflection off Curran to mid-on

Kaverappa to Kohli, SIX, Kohli gives the charge and plays a superb lofted drive over mid-off for six! Fuller than a length, he gets close enough and hits through the line with a clean swing of the bat

Kaverappa to Kohli, 1 run, looks to go down the ground again after stepping out, but Kaverappa cramps him up a touch by bowling into the pads. Kohli drags it off the inside half to deep backward square
Kaverappa to Will Jacks, no run, Jacks makes room but Kaverappa follows him! Back of a length delivery slanted in, cramps Jacks for room and cuts him in half
Kaverappa to Will Jacks, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Kaverappa to Will Jacks, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! Kaverappa punches the air in delight as he gets his second wicket. Slower ball on the pads, Jacks looks to sweep but fails to get it past short fine. Good catch from Harshal diving to his left there as the dangerous Jacks goes. Will Jacks c Harshal Patel b Kaverappa 12(7) [4s-1 6s-1]
Rajat Patidar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Kaverappa to Rajat Patidar, no run, back of a length on middle, Patidar tucks it to midwicket

Kaverappa to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, could've been 'caught Harshal bowled Kaverappa' again, but the catch goes down this time! Third dropped catch from PBKS in just the fifth over. Back of a length on middle, Patidar pulls it in the air and Harshal gets to it at deep backward square. But he can't hold on while on the move
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, no run, slower ball first ball from Harshal, Patidar knocks it down the pitch
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, 138.5kph, pitched up on middle, almost a half-volley and Patidar flicks it nicely through midwicket
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, beautifully played! Good length outside off, Patidar waits in the crease, plays late and chops it past the keeper while also beating short third
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, no run, back of a length on off, not short enough and Patidar miscues the pull in the air. But it falls well short of mid-on
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, FOUR, half-volley on middle at 138kph, Patidar gets forward and drives it sweetly down the ground
Harshal Patel to Rajat Patidar, no run, good length ball outside off, Patidar looks to drive through the off-side but the ball straightens a touch and beats the edge

Timeout! Despite dropping three catches, PBKS have managed to pick up a couple of crucial wickets - both falling to debutant Kaverappa. He should've had Kohli and Patidar too, but didn't get support from his fielders. Could've been a different picture had those catches been taken.

Highlights (Overs 1-6): -- Ashutosh drops Kohli on nought -- Kaverappa gets rid of Faf in his 2nd over -- Curran concedes 16 off his 1st over -- Rossouw drops (relatively tough chance) Kohli on 10 -- Kaverappa nips out Jacks with a slower ball -- Patidar dropped on 0 by Harshal -- All 3 drops off the bowling of Kaverappa

Kaverappa to Kohli, SIX, bottom hand comes off but the connection is still good enough! One-handed six from Kohli! Full on middle, he gives the charge, hits through the line over mid-off and clears the ropes easily
Kaverappa to Kohli, 1 run, pushed wide of mid-off for a single
Kaverappa to Rajat Patidar, SIX, length ball on off, Patidar gets a small stride forward and lofts it down the ground. He clears the long-on boundary comfortably. Made it look so easy there
Kaverappa to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, short of length on off, Patidar tucks it into the on-side
Kaverappa to Kohli, 1 run, slanted into the pads, Kohli clips it through midwicket
Kaverappa to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, slower ball floated up on middle, Patidar flicks it to deep midwicket. Kaverappa bowls out with 2/36!
Rahul Chahar, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, SIX, Chahar starts with a half-tracker and gets punished! It's pulled away fiercely over long-on for a 95-meter six!
Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, SIX, another half-tracker, this time on leg stump, and it goes sailing over the square leg boundary as Patidar rocks back and nails the pull shot

Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, no run, dropped! Very difficult chance as it took a reasonable deflection off the edge. Flat length ball outside off, Patidar looks to cut but it's not short enough and he edges it through. Bairstow can't hold on
Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, no run, left alone outside off. Patidar perhaps expected a wide but it was well within the marker

Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, SIX, third six of the over, this time off the front foot! Full outside off, Patidar gets forward and lofts it beautifully over wide long-off. He can be destructive against spin as he's shown earlier in the season as well
Rahul Chahar to Rajat Patidar, no run, flat length ball darted in on leg, Patidar looks to clip it away but it brushes his pad
Arshdeep Singh [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, FOUR, short of length delivery slanted into the body from round the wicket, no great pace on it and not high enough to trouble Kohli either. He gets on top of the bounce and smashes the pull through square leg

Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, 1 run, short of length delivery just outside off, Kohli dabs to short third and goes across for a tight single. Would've been close at the striker's end if there was a direct hit
Rajat Patidar vs leg spin in IPL 2024 48 balls 127 runs 1 dismissal 4s/6s - 4/15 SR 264.58
Arshdeep Singh to Rajat Patidar, SIX, Patidar is in the zone! This isn't short at all, but he leans back and nails a straight-batted pull over wide long-on. Incredible shot!
Arshdeep Singh to Rajat Patidar, wide, full and wide, left alone, and it's called wide. Not sure about that decision
Arshdeep Singh to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, good length outside off, Patidar hangs back and knocks it to deep point
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, 1 run, short of length outside off, Kohli slaps it in the air and it falls wide of sweeper cover who cuts it off on the bounce

Arshdeep Singh to Rajat Patidar, 2 runs, excellent stop in the deep from Ashutosh! Full and wide, Patidar reaches out and creams it through extra cover. Was racing away to the boundary but Ashutosh was equal to it, diving across to his right and cutting it off
Sam Curran [1.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Kohli, FOUR, close to a yorker outside off, but it's put away to the boundary as Kohli just opens the face and slices it past short third
Sam Curran to Kohli, 1 run, Kohli steps out, gets too close to the pitch of it and squeezes it to long-on

Sam Curran to Rajat Patidar, SIX, fifty off just 21 balls for Patidar! Short at the body, he goes for the pull and gets it away over short fine. The ball seemed to climb on him and he may not have been in control, but it flies for six. Kohli walks over to him and gives him a hug
Sam Curran to Rajat Patidar, 1 run, full outside off, driven to long-off
Sam Curran to Kohli, 1 run, slower short ball, Kohli miscues the pull in the air but it falls wide of deep midwicket
There's some rain in the air
Sam Curran to Rajat Patidar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Sam Curran to Rajat Patidar, out Caught by Bairstow!! Curran screams in celebration as he gets rid of Patidar. Full and wide, makes him reach out on the drive drive and he gets a healthy edge to the keeper. End of a brilliant knock that's given RCB a massive boost. Rajat Patidar c Bairstow b Sam Curran 55(23) [4s-3 6s-6]

Cameron Green, right handed bat, comes to the crease

20:46 Local Time, 15:16 GMT, 20:46 IST: Play to resume at 8.55pm local
Okay, players are out in the middle again, all set to go. Livingstone has the ball in hand
Livingstone to Kohli, 1 run, juicy full toss on middle, and Kohli is happy to just knock it to long-on for a single
Livingstone to Green, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Livingstone to Kohli, wide, drifting down leg, Kohli looks to sweep but misses
Livingstone to Kohli, no run, length ball on off, hint of turn, Kohli looks to cut but chops it to point
Livingstone to Kohli, no run, length ball on off, Kohli gets forward to defend but it grips and turns away past the edge. Kohli has a smile on his face
Livingstone to Kohli, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Livingstone to Green, 2 runs, another full toss, and again it's only knocked down the ground for a single. Oh wait, what's happened there? Looks like there's an overthrow and they get back for two
Rahul Chahar [1.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Kohli, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Rahul Chahar to Green, FOUR, full outside off, Green gets forward and strikes it sweetly over extra cover, hitting with the turn
Rahul Chahar to Green, no run, flat on leg stump, back of a length, Green is cramped for room and punches to midwicket
Rahul Chahar to Green, 1 run, low full toss on off, Green gets forward and drives to long-on
Rahul Chahar to Kohli, 2 runs, overpitched on off, Kohli drives firmly but the fielder at extra cover gets a hand on it while diving across. Takes pace off, allowing long-off to cut it off
Rahul Chahar to Kohli, no run, full ball on off, driven to extra cover
Livingstone to Green, no run, 92.7kph, full on middle and leg, turning away, Green gets forward and drives back to Livingstone

Livingstone to Green, 1 run, full ball on middle, Green looks to whip it through the on-side but the ball grips a touch. He gets a thick leading edge that goes flying to the left of Livingstone and down to long-off
Livingstone to Kohli, 1 run, flat length ball just outside off, Kohli dabs it to short third
Livingstone to Green, 1 run, full on the stumps, pushed to long-on
Livingstone to Kohli, FOUR, overpitched on middle and leg, and Kohli puts it away! He clears the front leg and hammers it through the gap at midwicket to bring up his fifty

Livingstone to Kohli, FOUR, goes for a big slog-sweep but doesn't get hold of it! However, it clears the leaping midwicket fielder in the infield and goes racing away wide of long-on. Desperate dive from Curran in the deep is in vain
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, low full toss on middle and leg, Green pushes the drive to the left of long-on
Harshal Patel to Kohli, 1 run, I0$ full toss outside off, Kohli whips it away to the right of mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Green, FOUR, width outside off at I0$, Green goes deep inside the crease and stabs it past the leaping right hand of backward point
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, yorker length on the stumps at I0$, Green jams the drive down to long-on
Harshal Patel to Kohli, 1 run, charges down the track and slashes the I0$ lengthg delivery to the left of sweeper cover
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, I0$ wobble seam full delivery outside off, Green biffs the drive to the right of long-off
Livingstone to Green, no run, quicker on the stumps, punched back to the bowler
Most 600+ run seasons in IPL 4 KL Rahul & Virat Kohli 3 C Gayle & D Warner 2 Faf du Plessis
Livingstone to Green, 1 run, fuller on leg stump, nudged away to the right of deep mid-wicket
Livingstone to Kohli, 1 run, stays inside the crease and dabs the flatter delivery to the right of short third
Livingstone to Green, 1 run, full on the stumps, Green lunges forward and pushes the drive to long-off
Livingstone to Kohli, SIX, quicker and fuller outside off, Kohli gets down on one knee and smokes the slogsweep flat over the mid-wicket fence. Crrrruunnnccchhhed....
Livingstone to Kohli, 2 runs, makes room and punches the short delivery to the right of long-off
Timeout! RCB will aim to post at least 220 from here, but can the Kings pull things back?
Sam Curran [2.0-0-29-1] is back into the attack
Sam Curran to Green, 1 run, full and wide of off at I0$, Green toe-ends the drive to the left of cover
Sam Curran to Kohli, SIX, whew! That was hit with some authority from Virat Kohli. Down on one knee, gets under the slower full delivery and deposits it into the second tier over mid-wicket for a I0$
Sam Curran to Kohli, wide, yorker length slips it well wide of off, Kohli looks to slice and misses
Sam Curran to Kohli, wide, full and slanting away outside off at I0$, Kohli lets it pass
Sam Curran to Kohli, 1 run, good length outside off at I0$, punched down the ground to the left of long-off
1000+ runs most opponents in IPL 3 Virat Kohli vs CSK, DC & PBKS 2 Rohit Sharma vs DC & KKR 2 David Warner vs KKR & PBKS
Sam Curran to Green, FOUR, I0$ overpitched on the stumps, Green clubs it back over the bowler's head with plenty of bottom hand power and the outfield takes care of the rest
Sam Curran to Green, 1 run, I0$ back of a length outside off, Green looks to go hard and chops it off the inside edge towards mid-off
Sam Curran to Kohli, SIX, full ball in the slot outside off at I0$, VK picked the change of pace and thrashed it with an air of nonchalance over long-on
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Green, FOUR, full and well wide of off-stump, Green throws his hands on the drive and gets a thick outside edge that flies in the gap between the keeper and short third
Harshal Patel to Green, SIX, that has disappeared into the night sky. Full and right in the slot around off, Green clears his front leg and tonks it down the ground for a 76-metre maximum
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, yorker length outside off, Green squeezes it down to mid-off
Harshal Patel to Kohli, wide, high full toss bowled wide of off, Kohli lets it go
Harshal Patel to Kohli, 1 run, fuller and wider of off, Kohli slices the lofted drive to the left of sweeper cover
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, full outside off at I0$, Green toe-ends the drive to the left of the bowler who manages to get a hand in his followthrough
Harshal Patel to Kohli, 1 run, 200 up for RCB. Kohli opens the bat face and punches the length delivery to deep cover
Jitesh, the impact sub, comes onto the field in place of Kaverappa
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-24-0] is back into the attack
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, no run, full and angled in towards off from round the wicket, Kohli drills it straight and ends up knocking the stumps at the non-striker's end
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, FOUR, plenty of width on offer and Kohli unfurls his classy cover drive in the gap to the left of extra cover. Supreme timing on that...
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, SIX, Kohli into the 90s... Hops on the back foot, opens the bat face and guides the short ball up and over backward point for a well-timed maximum
Stat: Fifth 200+ total by RCB in IPL 2024 - their most in a season surpassing four in IPL 2016
Switches to over the wicket now
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, wide, goes full and well wide of off, Kohli shoulders arms
Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Arshdeep Singh to Kohli, out Caught by Rossouw!! BREAKING NEWS: Punjab Kings have taken a catch. They did drop five earlier, but will feel mighty relieved with the wicket of Kohli. Arshdeep Singh kept it wide of off stump and the length wasn't too full either. Kohli looks to flay on the off-side and slices it off the thick outside half low to the left of sweeper cover. Rossouw keeps his calm and takes a fine catch. Kohli c Rossouw b Arshdeep Singh 92(47) [4s-7 6s-6]
29th 200+ total conceded by PBKS in IPL - the most by a team going past 28 by RCB
Stat: Only the second instance of Virat Kohli getting dismissed in the 90s in IPL. The first was 99 vs Delhi Capitals in Delhi in 2013.
Dinesh Karthik, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Arshdeep Singh to Karthik, no run, bumper angled in at the body, Karthik misses the pull and takes a blow on his shoulder
Arshdeep Singh to Karthik, SIX, overcooks the full delivery and this time DK is prepared for it. Went deep inside the crease and smashed it many-a-mile over deep extra cover
Rahul Chahar [2.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Rahul Chahar to Green, FOUR, quicker and shorter outside off, Green backs away a touch and slaps it off the strong botttom hand, beating the desperate dive of long-off to his left
Rahul Chahar to Green, 1 run, fast and flat on the stumps, Green slogs and gets a thick inside edge into the leg-side
Most runs by an Indian batter for RCB 7897 Virat Kohli 900* Dinesh Karthik 898 Rahul Dravid 884 Devdutt Padikkal 731 Parthiv Patel
Rahul Chahar to Karthik, SIX, quicker and in the arc outside off, Karthik gets under the fuller length and swats it away for a 78-metre maximum over mid-wicket
Rahul Chahar to Karthik, 1 run, quick and wide of off, Karthik shuffles across and gets an inside edge on the sweep to the left of short fine

Rahul Chahar to Green, 3 runs, quicker outside off, Green makes room and gets a thick under edge on the cut to the left of short third. Harshal gives chase and manages to pull theg ball back inches inside the ropes...

Rahul Chahar to Karthik, no ball, FOUR, oh dear! It's getting bad to worse for the Punjab Kings. DK gets low and hammers the slogsweep to the left of deep mid-wicket. Rossouw tries his best with a well-timed slide, but couldn't gather the ball due to an awkward bounce. To make matters worse, Rahul Chahar has overstepped...
Rahul Chahar to Karthik, 1 run, Rahul Chahar throws the freehit ball wide of off stump, Karthik looks to power it for a six and slices it straight to the man at deep extra cover
Harshal Patel [3.0-0-36-0] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Karthik, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Karthik, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Harshal Patel gets his 1st wicket. Digs the short ball around off, Karthik looks to pull and gets a thcik top-edge that's been snaffled by the fielder at long-on. DK was a touch late on the shot and Curran did well to cover a few yards to his right in the deep. Karthik c Sam Curran b Harshal Patel 18(7) [4s-1 6s-2]
PBKS review for lbw: Lomror is the man in question. NO bat involved confirms UltraEdge. Wickets missing on ball tracker. Not out...
Mahipal Lomror, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Lomror, leg byes, 1 run, yorker angled in towards middle and leg, Lomror couldn't get under it and the ball deflects to the right of mid-wicket for a quick single
Harshal Patel to Green, 1 run, length outside off, Green backs away and forces the drive wide of cover
Harshal Patel to Lomror, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harshal Patel to Lomror, out Bowled!! Slower ball yorker that dips cunningly at the last moment to deceive Lomror all ends up on the under edge. He was deep inside the crease looking to power it on the leg-side, but no dice. Lomror b Harshal Patel 0(2)
Swapnil Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshal Patel to Swapnil Singh, 1 run, full toss on the stumps, Swapnil heaves it to the right of deep mid-wicket. Thinks of a second, but Green wasn't interested...
Harshal Patel to Green, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshal Patel to Green, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Ends with three does Harshal Patel. Bowls it slow and full outside off, Green fetches the slog and drags it off the toe end of the bat. Curran runs across to his right at long-on and times his slide to absolute perfection before completing the catch. Green c Sam Curran b Harshal Patel 46(27) [4s-5 6s-1]

21:48 local, 16:18 GMT, 21:48 IST: 119/3 before the rain break. And 122/4 after the rain break. Both of them in the span of 10 overs precisely. Vidhwath Kaverappa was terrific with the new ball on debut and bowled much better than what his figures suggest. At least 3 catches were dropped during his bowling, and, despite that, got 2 crucial wickets inside the powerplay. Patidar smoked a 21-ball fifty, and DK offered the finishing touches like he usually does. Kohli got to his fifty off 32 balls, but stepped on the accelerator by hammering 40 off his next 15 balls. Cam Green too played a key part in RCB posting a 220-plus total. That said, will the drop chances come back to hauntthe hosts? We will have the answers shortly...

Welcome back! Yash Dayal comes in as the impact sub for RCB. Patidar sits out. Swapnil Singh to kickstart proceedings. No slips...

Kohli: Was important for me to keep up the strike rate right through (laughs). I was just focussed on taking the momentum forward. There was a tricky phase when Rajat got out, and there was a break for rain and hail. We had a bit of stop of momentum. Had to rebuild for 8-10 balls. Once the base was set and Cam got a few boundaries away, I thought I had to go again. Surface was pretty dry underneath, and there was some grass coverage as well. If you saw Faf and me got done by lack of pace off the pitch. There was a two-paced feel with the new ball, which I think is a great opportunities for our bowlers to make early inroads and exploit that swing out there. We thought anything over 230 would be a good total here. That was the only mindset. That was a hell of an over from Harshal in the last over otherwise we would've been 250-plus. Difficult to analyse someone in one game (talking about Kaverappa). He has swing in his hand. That's the thing when you're playing your first game and people haven't played you - you get away with it. You try to figure out variations and stuff like that. Kudos to him - he bowled good areas. But after the three overs when he came for the fourth, we knew the swing's done and then we went after him.
